In the past studies, the economic sectors have been widely investigated based on the random matrix theory \cite{pan07,gop01,she09}.Business sectors can be identified for most mature markets, except for the Chinese stock market. The stocks of the Chinese stock market are identified by the ST and Blue-chip sectors \cite{she09}. To understand how the geography affects the financial dynamics, here we apply the random matrix theory to revealing the geographical sector. Based on the stock correlations of the price returns in Eq. (3), the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of the correlation matrix $\texttt{C}$ are analyzed. By searching for the dominant components in the eigenvectors of the first several largest eigenvalues, the geographical sectors can be identified.

